      "lesson title": "Ransomware Impact on Logistics and Shipping",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how ransomware attacks affect the logistics and shipping industry, with a particular focus on the growing reliance on AI-driven systems to manage supply chains, route planning, and cargo tracking. As more organisations adopt automated and interconnected technologies, a single ransomware incident can cascade rapidly across operations, causing widespread delays, financial losses, and reputational damage. You will learn about real-world examples of attacks that have brought major shipping companies to a standstill, and understand why AI-dependent infrastructure can amplify the scale of disruption rather than reduce it. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer picture of the vulnerabilities that exist within modern logistics networks and why cybersecurity awareness is essential for everyone working in this sector.",
